<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-087-556  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 087 556.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  March 6 1989 v6 n9 p25(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users need just plain English for Britton Lee DBMS queries.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kovsky, Steven.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Britton Lee Inc has announced that its ShareBase database systemswill begin to use front-end products from Natural Language Inc(NLI) that will allow users to structure their database queries instandard English.andP;  The ShareBase products, which consist ofrelational database management system software and StructuredQuery Language database server systems, will be provided with aneasy-to-use front end that allows access to shared data resourcesby typing questions in ordinary, conversational English.andP;  An NLIConnector will support ShareBase for VAX computers running VMS andSun Microsystems workstations.andP;  The enhanced products are aimed atexecutives who have little computer knowledge.andP;  The NaturalLanguage interface to the ShareBase server is priced at $7,000 to$50,000, depending on the size of the ShareBase system.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Britton Lee Inc. (product development)Natural Language Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    BLII.andO;Product:   ShareBase (Data base management system) (product development).andO;Topic:     Data Base Management SystemsSimplicityNatural Language InterfacesCooperative Agreement.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Users Need Just Plain English For Britton Lee DBMS QueriesandM;LOS GATOS, Calif.andP;  -- Britton Lee's ShareBase database systems will startspeaking English as a result of an agreement with Natural Language Inc.andO;(NLI).andM;Britton Lee has announced that its relational database management systemsoftware and SQL database server systems now will be supported by NaturalLanguage front-end products that allow users to structure their databasequeries in standard English.andM;NLI's Natural Language package provides an easy-to-use front end that allowsaccess to shared data resources through the typing of simple questions inordinary, conversational English, according to a Britton Lee spokesman.andM;An NLI Connector will support ShareBase for VAX computers running VMS and SunMicrosystems workstations, the spokesman said.andP;  The ease-of-use featuresincorporated in NLI's front end should make databases less intimidating, evenfor corporate executives who traditionally rely on their computer-literatesubordinates for data access.andM;&quot;NLI's technology will help expand our marketplace to the executive's desktop and beyond by allowing users without SQL savvy to have access to data,&quot;said John Cavalier, Britton Lee's president and chief executive officer.andM;Only the BeginningandM;NLI's president, Tania Amochaev, suggested that the agreement with BrittonLee covering ShareBase support for VAX/VMS could be the first step in alucrative partnership.andM;&quot;Britton Lee's client/server architecture is well-suited to relationaldatabase management,&quot; Amochaev said.andP;  &quot;We expect to see a large number ofsophisticated ShareBase applications with our English-language front end inthe future.&quot;andM;The Natural Language interface to the ShareBase server is priced at $7,000 to$50,000, depending on the size of the ShareBase system.andP;  Natural Language forShareBase on VAX/VMS and sun workstations is available now.andM;Britton Lee Inc. designs relational database software and high-performanceSQL database server systems for multivendor environments.andP;  The company islocated at 14600 Winchester Blvd., Los Gatos, CA 95030, (408) 378-7000.andM;Natural Language Inc. develops and markets database tools and interfaces thatlet users access computer information using conversational Endlish.andP;  Thecompany is located at 2910 Seventh St., Berkeley, CA 94710, (415) 841-3500.andO;</TEXT></DOC>